lead_paragraph: James A. Baker, the F.B.I.’s general counsel, said the bureau was still working on putting the extracted data to use.

headline.print_headline: F.B.I. Lawyer Won’t Say If Data From Unlocked iPhone Is Useful
headline.main: F.B.I. Lawyer Won’t Say if Data From Unlocked iPhone Is Useful

snippet: James A. Baker, the F.B.I.’s general counsel, said the bureau was still working on putting the extracted data to use.
abstract: FBI general counsel James A Baker offers bit more insight into data contained on iPhone used by one of San Bernardino, Calif, terrorists, which became focus of monumental legal fight between agency and Apple; Baker does not indicate whether data has been deemed useful.
